OL,3,CJersey's Chief Minister wants to stand
OL,4,Cwith Guernsey after ferry clash
OL,6,FJersey's Chief Minister has written to
OL,7,Fhis Guernsey counterpart in an attempt
OL,8,Fto ease tensions after Deputy Lyndon
OL,9,FTrott called for an end to an alleged
OL,10,F"campaign of misinformation" about the
OL,11,Fjoint ferry tender process.
OL,13,FIn his letter, Deputy Lyndon Farnham
OL,14,Fsays the Governments of Jersey and
OL,15,FGuernsey "must move forward
OL,16,Fpositively" and "stand together",
OL,17,Fexpressing regret that the islands
OL,18,Fwent separate ways in choosing a ferry
OL,19,Foperator as Jersey chose Danish firm
OL,20,FDFDS and Guernsey went with Brittany
OL,21,FFerries.
