OL,3,CJersey's Chief Minister wants to stand
OL,4,Cwith Guernsey after ferry clash
OL,6,FAs reported in the Guernsey Press,
OL,7,FDeputy Trott claimed there had been
OL,8,F"unsubstantiated and untrue statements
OL,9,Fabout the States of Guernsey" by
OL,10,FJersey officials, criticism that
OL,11,FJersey's top politician is now trying
OL,12,Fto ease.
OL,14,FDuring a scrutiny panel hearing about
OL,15,Fthe ferry procurement process on 12
OL,16,FMarch, Jersey's Chief Economy Officer
OL,17,FRichard Corrigan had claimed that
OL,18,FGuernsey was never "openly" committed
OL,19,Fto working with Jersey to a tender
OL,20,Fprocess that might result in a change
OL,21,Fof operator for both islands.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/7
